# Copilot Instructions Extract

**Source**: `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (v1.8) — the **canonical** reference for all AI assistants in this repository. This file provides a concise summary; when in doubt, defer to the source.

---

## Repository Context

**Data Preprocessing** — academic workspace for data cleaning, transformation, and pipeline concepts (M.Sc. DSAI). Not a web application. Not a production system.

**Owner**: Swamy PKV (M.Sc. Data Science & AI).

---

## Seven-layer week companion architecture (this repo only)

**Full contract**: [09_week-companion-architecture.mdc](./09_week-companion-architecture.mdc)
**Naming patterns**: [07_file-naming-conventions.mdc](./07_file-naming-conventions.mdc)

For each **week in the repo**, maintain **seven** companion files in `weeks/weekN/`:

1. `01_reading-notes.md` — theory (first-person learning journey voice)
2. `02_examples.md` — worked examples (original scenarios)
3. `03_quiz.md` — self-assessment (original synthesis only)
4. `04_notebook.ipynb` — hands-on experiments
5. `05_model-paper.md` — exam-style readiness
6. `06_discussion.md` — reflection / forum prompts
7. `07_assignment.md` — structured weekly deliverables

**Weeks on demand** — only add files for weeks you are building. All eight weeks (1–8) are fully migrated to `weeks/week1/` through `weeks/week8/`.

**Learning flow**: theory → examples → quiz → notebook → model paper → discussion prompt → assignment.

